Feature: k8infra API smoke migration to RestAssured

Contract IDs
- `CID-LOGIN-HELLOWORLD`
- `CID-MBOOKS-LOCATIONS`

Functional requirements
- Add a Java RestAssured smoke suite under `k8infra`.
- Coverage must include:
  - `POST /login/HelloWorld`
  - `GET /login/admin`
  - `GET /login/activeSessions`
  - `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/locations`
  - `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/hello`
- Preserve iOS-compatible login HMAC behavior used by Python smoke tests.
- Support config overrides via system properties and env vars.

Acceptance criteria
- RestAssured smoke tests run with `mvn test` in `k8infra/api-smoke-restassured`.
- Existing smoke scenarios from Python scripts are represented in Java tests.
- `k8infra` docs point to RestAssured as primary framework.
- Python scripts are marked as legacy fallback.

Definition of Done
- [ ] Spec + implementation + tested evidence present.
- [ ] `@testing-engineer` verification completed.
- [ ] `@security-specialist` verification completed.
- [ ] `@performance-engineer` verification completed.

